Klasse Ephemora was a Chiss space explorer. Several centuries before, he discovered a system, which became his namesake.

Ilum is the ice planet home to many of the Adegan crystals used in the construction of Jedi lightsabers. The caverns containing the crystals were long ago turned into a Jedi temple.

In 22 BBY, it was the location of the Battle of Ilum. After the fall of the Galactic Republic, the Galactic Empire established a base on the planet to intercept any Jedi who might return for lightsaber crystals.

Ilum was long used by Jedi as a location to find crystals for lightsaber construction. To ensure the security of the planet and the crystals, the planet has been left off of starcharts for that very reason. Because its existence was not known generally to non-Jedi, Ilum is virtually forgotten after the destruction of the Jedi and Palpatine's information purges. This gave the remaining Jedi a safe harbor.

Csilla, the homeworld of the Chiss, is a cold world of glaciers and snowy wastes located deep within Chiss Space, and serves as the capital of the Chiss Ascendancy.

The planet entered an ice age in 5,000 BBY. Glaciers covered the normally-warm equatorial regions of the planet, while solid ice locked the poles in perpetual winter. In order to survive, the Chiss built energy-efficient warrens beneath the ice, as close to the warmth of the inner planet as possible, with underground carriage travel routes to connect the various underground sections of Csilla. The iceways were bored through the bedrock of the planet, so that they were unaffected by the shifting ice found on the planet's surface.

Lehon, also referes to as Rakata, Rakata Prime, and the Unknown World, is the homeworld of the Rakata species and the capital of their Infinite Empire.

Lehon is a tropical world that inhabits a remote and relatively unknown corner of the Galaxy. Its surface is largely covered by oceans which are dotted by numerous clusters of islands and archipelagos. It is the only planet in the Lehon system, but it shares an orbit around its primary star with the Star Forge, an ancient Rakatan space station and factory which draws its fuel directly from the system's primary star. The planet itself is orbited by two small moons, but one of them is close enough to be visible from the surface during daylight, covering a significant portion of the sky.
